lens_galaxy.py is a simple code
to simulate an image of elliptical
galaxy from SDSS survey.

The input paramters are:
1, R_eff,     the desired effective radius in arcsec
2, VelDis,    velocity dispersion of the dark matter halo
3, NoiseVar,  variance of the noise in terms of count^2.
4, NoiseType, Gaussian or Poisson
5, zl,        redshift of the lens
6, E,         ellipticity of the lens
7, Phi,       Orientation of the lens wrt the North

$./lens_galaxy.py --NoiseType Gaussian --E 0.3 --Phi 45 --R_eff 5 --zl 0.35 --VelDis 300
will give you a postage-stamp of 128x128 galaxy with de Vaucouleurs profile determined
by the parameters you set.

By Wentao Luo Dec. 18 2015
at CMU
